data.meta_description:
33 likes, 1 comments - judygarlandmuseum on August 14, 2015: "WELCOME TO THE JUDY GARLAND MUSEUM PART 2: (re: Garland's birthplace & home for her first 4 yrs.) Everything in the house predates 1925 and is a mix of family-heirloom-type pieces—European porcelains, Axminster-style rugs, silver candlesticks, American Empire furniture—plus “modern” touches, such as a Victrola record player in the living room that would have been “the zenith of chic,” designer Mark Charbonnet says. —Architectural Digest | For more info. visit www.judygarlandmuseum.com. 
#judyGarland #judygarlandmuseum #interiorDesign #rubyslippers #wizardOfOz #dorothy #onlyinmn".
